---
title: Breadcrumb
---

p.-text Breadcrumbs are used to help users identify where they are in a sites page hierarchy.

h3 Examples
p.-text To render a breadcrumb, use the class <code>a-breadcrumb</code>.

h4 Base
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    nav.a-breadcrumb.-text(aria-label="Breadcrumb")
      ol
        li.a-breadcrumb__item
          a(href='#') Parent
        li.a-breadcrumb__item
          a(href='#') Child 1
        li.a-breadcrumb__item.-active
          a(href='#',aria-current="page") Child 2
  :code(lang="html")
    <nav class="a-breadcrumb -text" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol>
          <li class="a-breadcrumb__item">
            <a href="#">Parent</a>
          </li>
          <li class="a-breadcrumb__item">
            <a href="#">Child 1</a>
          </li>
          <li class="a-breadcrumb__item -active">
            <a href="#" aria-current="page">Child 2</a>
          </li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

